   On his wife, the artist and musician Laurie Anderson, whose remembrance
   of Reed is one of the most soul-stirring meditations on love and loss
   ever written (“And death? I believe that the purpose of death is the
   release of love.”):

   IFRAME:
   https://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=https%3A//api.soundcloud.com/track
   s/119646680&auto_play=false&hide_related=false&visual=true

     She’s so smart and can do anything — anything she does is absolutely
     great. It’s amazing.

   On balancing raw force and raw vulnerability in his music and writing:

   IFRAME:
   https://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=https%3A//api.soundcloud.com/track
   s/119647777&auto_play=false&hide_related=false&visual=true

     I like conflict — it’s balance. Or, like tai chi, balance is like
     the yin and the yang. Even a song like “Perfect Day” — the kick is
     at the end, the last verse: “I thought I was someone else, someone
     good.”

